				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">True.  I can get it working using the hack mentioned in the original post.  But, I might as well shoot for a higher goal.<br /><br />Looking at this stuff makes me wonder how the developers of SMB1 ended up using these facilities.  The Famicom came out a few years earlier and none of the launch titles resemble anything like SMB1.  During those first few years, devs must have recognized the shortcomings of the system such as a lack of a scanline interrupts forcing them to invent the sprite 0 hit test.  The scroll offsets were probably only designed for being modified between frames until someone discovered how to get around that.  Sigh.  Long story short, emulating this is going to be challenge.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

