				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I implemented everything in Loopy's &quot;The skinny on NES scrolling&quot; document and now it works perfectly <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />  Amazing!  <br /><br />I suspect that a full implementation probably was not necessary; the writes to $2005 and $2006 suggest that the SMB1 devs really did not intend to fully exploit the PPU registers.  Rather, they simply needed the base nametable address reset to $2000 at the start of each frame and they must have noticed at some point that were doing that indirectly, saving them the extra code to do it directly.  I could have sorted out the values written to $2005 and $2006 and made this work, but what's the point.  Loopy's solution is a far more general solution and it certainly works well.</div>

